<Link id="l00149" /><CodeLine lineNumber="149"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Features table</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00150" /><CodeLine lineNumber="150"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// --------------</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00151" /><CodeLine lineNumber="151"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For each interfering live range (incl. the candidate) we collect a number of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00152" /><CodeLine lineNumber="152"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// features. However, because the features are of different types (and because</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00153" /><CodeLine lineNumber="153"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// of ML best practices), we organize the tensors per feature, not per</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00154" /><CodeLine lineNumber="154"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// candidate. Each such tensor has a scalar value corresponding to the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00155" /><CodeLine lineNumber="155"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// interferring live range at that position, in the order in AllocationOrder.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00156" /><CodeLine lineNumber="156"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The last position corresponds to the virt reg seeking allocation.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00157" /><CodeLine lineNumber="157"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Exception to all that is the progression feature, which is just a scalar (see</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00158" /><CodeLine lineNumber="158"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// its documentation for details).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00159" /><CodeLine lineNumber="159"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Note on naming: the &quot;&#95;by&#95;max&quot; are normalized using the largest value of that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00160" /><CodeLine lineNumber="160"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// tensor, as observed in the current decision making stage (i.e. for the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00161" /><CodeLine lineNumber="161"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// current call to the advisor&#39;s tryFindEvictionCandidate)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00162" /><CodeLine lineNumber="162"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00163" /><CodeLine lineNumber="163"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The feature list format: type, name, shape, documentation.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00164" /><CodeLine lineNumber="164"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Note: we can really just use int64 and float, hence the modeling of some</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00165" /><CodeLine lineNumber="165"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// bools as int64 values.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00166" /><CodeLine lineNumber="166"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define RA&#95;EVICT&#95;FEATURES&#95;LIST(M)                                              \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00167" /><CodeLine lineNumber="167"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">  M(int64&#95;t, mask, PerLiveRangeShape,                                          \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00168" /><CodeLine lineNumber="168"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">    &quot;boolean values, 0 for unavailable candidates (i.e. if a position is 0, &quot;  \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00169" /><CodeLine lineNumber="169"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">    &quot;it &quot;                                                                      \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="170"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">    &quot;can&#39;t be evicted)&quot;)                                                       \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="171"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">  M(int64&#95;t, is&#95;free, PerLiveRangeShape,                                       \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="172"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">    &quot;boolean values, 1 if this phys reg is actually free (no interferences)&quot;)  \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="173"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">  M(float, nr&#95;urgent, PerLiveRangeShape,                                       \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="174"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">    &quot;number of &#39;urgent&#39; intervals, normalized. Urgent are those that are OK &quot;  \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="175"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">    &quot;to break cascades&quot;)                                                       \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="176"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">  M(float, nr&#95;broken&#95;hints, PerLiveRangeShape,                                 \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="177"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">    &quot;if this position were evicted, how many broken hints would there be&quot;)     \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="178"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">  M(int64&#95;t, is&#95;hint, PerLiveRangeShape,                                       \\</span></CodeLine>
